The article is a transcript of a conversation between Vice President Kamala Harris and two climate scientists, Dr. Marshall Shepherd and Dr. Isaiah Bolden. They discuss the progress made in addressing climate change in the last two years, the need for a whole-of-community and whole-of-government approach, and the importance of addressing climate issues in an equitable and just manner. They also highlight the significance of investments in clean energy, such as electric vehicles and infrastructure, and the impact of climate change on public health, particularly in marginalized communities. The conversation emphasizes the urgency of taking action on climate change and the role that young leaders and interdisciplinary approaches play in finding solutions.